<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>Garbage disposals are one of the most cost-effective appliance repairs in Los Angeles — and one of the most commonly misdiagnosed. A humming disposal that won't turn is almost always a jammed grinding plate, not a failed motor. A disposal that won't start at all often has a tripped reset button or a blown fuse from the switch circuit. Neither requires a replacement part.</p>
<p>We diagnose first. For a humming or jammed disposal, we assess whether the impeller can be freed (most of the time it can), whether the motor windings are intact, and whether the unit is worth repairing vs. replacing. InSinkErator and Moen disposals under 8 years old are almost always worth repairing. Older units where the motor has seized are evaluated honestly — sometimes a new unit makes more sense.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tip-block">
      <div class="tip-label">🔧 Try this before calling — the reset button</div>
      <p>If your disposal is completely dead with no humming sound: look under the sink on the bottom of the disposal unit for a small red or black button — the thermal overload reset. Press it firmly until you feel a click. Then try the switch. This resolves about 30% of 'dead disposal' calls at no cost. If it still doesn't start after the reset, call us.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
